adjectives.description: blocked (comparative more blocked, superlative most blocked)

entries.meaning: Obstructed, so that through movement or flow is prevented or impeded.
examples: This road is blocked, so we must find another route.
Call a plumber to unclog the blocked drain.

entries.meaning: Unable to move owing to an obstruction.
examples: The argument was over a blocked car in a driveway.

entries.meaning: (of a person, telephone number, IP address, etc.) Banned or barred from connecting or logging on.
examples: Blocked users will be unable to access their accounts indefinitely.
The phone will reject calls from blocked numbers.

entries.meaning: (of a computer account or similar) Disabled or disconnected, so as to prevent access.
examples: All of this user's accounts are now blocked.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of block
